metadata.name: Warped #18
metadata.description:
A free little toy.  Play with it and it might make art!  This is my second project using a shader.  It starts by making a simple drawing, then the shader uses noise to warp the image.  I'm making it free because 1) You really have to work at it to make art (but I think it's a lot of fun to tinker with!), and 2) the capture sometimes has minor variances from the final image - couldn't figure it out.  Made with p5js and uses some Perlin noise code by Inigo Quilez.  

After opening, press "s" to save a large jpg.

metadata.name: Mustachioed #65
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.
Mustachioed is a historical research that aims to link the history of the mustache to the digital world.
Each piece of mustachioed is a ticket to enter this unique world where different samples of mustaches are collected.
Who has the chance to register an outstanding mustache to their names?
We must wait and see.
This research will continue!

Collection of unique men with weird mustaches. Including 13 traits and 473 Attributes.

metadata.name: bRAIN MAN #12
metadata.description:
This project is Generative Layered PNGs files.
There are 6 layers.
00-background - background color
01-body - face and body
02-wear - clothes
03-onmouth - things on mouth
04-onface - eyes wear
05-onhand - holding something

All pixel arts 80x80px pngs were manually drawing by me.
